ameters":{"content":"### Keep Valid Conversations\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Frame the Assignment","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"8bf6df40-74a1-e6e8-2716-67f81dac7d93","name":"Note: Keep Valid Conversations"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Frame the Assignment\n\nShapes the item: writes `assignment`, `deadline`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Coordinator Agent","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"f0546748-c350-d5cb-9459-e2591e99b9e0","name":"Note: Frame the Assignment"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Coordinator Agent\n\nThe AI brain: reads the input, decides which attached tools to call (and in what order), then composes the answer.\n\nPorts: ①→ Unpack Sections · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"1552ac09-e413-1f33-d6dd-b1a152581b72","name":"Note: Coordinator Agent"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Coordinator Agent** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"0616b728-3bc9-aab9-30d7-1963058ef746","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Research Specialist (Sub-workflow)\n\nSpecialist sub-workflow exposed as a callable tool — one narrow capability per tool.\n\nFeeds **Coordinator Agent** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[804,1510],"id":"392176ec-cbb5-4b90-8d85-f1a6472ada25","name":"Note: Research Specialist (Sub-workflow)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Draft Specialist (Sub-workflow)\n\nSpecialist sub-workflow exposed as a callable tool — one narrow capability per tool.\n\nFeeds **Coordinator Agent** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1060,1750],"id":"2a83dece-c3ac-1c58-541d-7dd8b374fb60","name":"Note: Draft Specialist (Sub-workflow)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Review Specialist (Sub-workflow)\n\nSpecialist sub-workflow exposed as a callable tool — one narrow capability per tool.\n\nFeeds **Coordinator Agent** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1492,1510],"id":"8e242007-02d4-51f5-4007-ce9230dadf07","name":"Note: Review Specialist (Sub-workflow)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enforce Result Schema\n\nForces the agent's answer into the JSON schema below — downstream nodes rely on this exact shape.\n\nFeeds **Coordinator Agent** as `outputParser`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1654,1090],"id":"c4bfb8ea-0fa5-2731-84e4-87cf44f4740b","name":"Note: Enforce Result Schema"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Unpack Sections\n\nExplodes the `output.sections` array into one item per element.\n\nNext: Persist Deliverable to Notion","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1978,520],"id":"0c09ff01-01b5-78fd-17c0-25980ab7b0e2","name":"Note: Unpack Sections"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Deliverable to Notion\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fingerprint for Idempotency · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2302,520],"id":"eac84459-5b17-e2c2-cc57-61a84d463777","name":"Note: Persist Deliverable to Notion"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per conversation (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2626,520],"id":"f5a8b6e9-5bf2-0622-ce33-8bcc740017bb","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2950,520],"id":"1b8d34db-39d5-9a17-c3df-5a4498897fbd","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3274,520],"id":"82b7ff28-0029-6a28-191c-8dca38f96bff","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3598,520],"id":"2eea231f-d526-95e2-3edd-da7e4aa51fc8","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3922,520],"id":"f62a0050-5957-331d-803d-a83767f4ae9c","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4246,520],"id":"55d3b039-14f9-93c0-e5db-29209bad4f35","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4570,520],"id":"4e1743c1-80ec-3ce1-e5b8-078825729c3e","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4894,520],"id":"ed279330-f5be-2b03-3b77-315051aa5e81","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5218,520],"id":"4be58ea7-cb0d-c5e8-cf59-f580cd70af27","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5542,520],"id":"fa3c4919-422e-68f7-3ed1-42d0ad40aa69","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nnotion — `getAll` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5866,520],"id":"7458b259-7085-0d7c-4b59-d027f8013d54","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Sort Conversations Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6190,520],"id":"3a0fb6a9-d50b-bde3-aedf-5bdcfc9c1224","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Conversations Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6514,520],"id":"3ae08c25-9d1f-a4cf-c0cc-1cb975950e16","name":"Note: Sort Conversations Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 25 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6838,520],"id":"d63dedde-4978-a7bf-7d9a-9d9ef22b9acb","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7162,520],"id":"3f27c14b-0c4c-b54b-2024-71eef46c89bd","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7486,520],"id":"65d889d0-a935-d5f9-98f1-d983ed7f4bd3","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7810,520],"id":"b15c3fbb-3f9a-8592-e6f0-f854926bc2f9","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8134,520],"id":"cd1cd588-3ed5-5a46-c74f-ca5ca11d848e","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8458,520],"id":"08a636e1-1043-4374-6189-9d37ed8a3656","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7810,1540],"id":"00db6bbb-aba5-cb75-2b55-67336d6f5d0b","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8134,1540],"id":"56cceb28-ece6-b495-554f-e5f81e16d15c","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8458,1540],"id":"a40691f0-3de1-b64a-4ff8-7d023f71fb16","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Answer chat messages for your team for Lead Bots (07732)\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nAnswer chat messages for your team for Lead Bots (07732). It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual lead bots is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Keep Valid Conversations → Frame the Assignment → Coordinator Agent → Unpack Sections → Persist Deliverable to Notion → Fingerprint for Idempotency → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating lead bots in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"f466899f-b8d1-af2b-4eab-9e7f1b56d8fc","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-20],"id":"d145cf9a-8c7f-3554-1d63-233a0bf8b094","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-20],"id":"df34c5b7-ab2d-70f5-b8db-d9f4e3858a24","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-20],"id":"eefa8f27-50a0-9e55-ed14-8fa1869653d6","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your lead bots process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-20],"id":"8a5f246d-30c9-279d-22bb-c969fbf62837","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"When Chat Message Received":{"main":[[{"node":"Keep Valid Conversations","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Keep Valid Conversations":{"main":[[{"node":"Frame the Assignment","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Frame the Assignment":{"main":[[{"node":"Coordinator Agent","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Coordinator Agent","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Research Specialist (Sub-workflow)":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Coordinator Agent","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Draft Specialist (Sub-workflow)":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Coordinator Agent","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Review Specialist (Sub-workflow)":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Coordinator Agent","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Enforce Result Schema":{"ai_outputParser":[[{"node":"Coordinator Agent","type":"ai_outputParser","index":0}]]},"Coordinator Agent":{"main":[[{"node":"Unpack Sections","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Unpack Sections":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Deliverable to Notion","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Deliverable to Notion":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Conversations Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Conversations Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"371759f1-2482-461f-8205-6590ca5032ae","id":"FDX07732"}